.PP
This function is intended primarily for sockets that are not connection oriented such as type \fIdgram\fR or \fIseqpacket\fR where messages may arrive from different source addresses.

.PP
Argument \fIBufSz\fR specifies the number of bytes for the receive buffer. If the buffer size is too small, the message will be truncated.

.PP
If \fIBufSz\fR is \fI0\fR, a default buffer size is used, which can be set by \fIsocket:setopt(Socket, {otp,recvbuf}, BufSz)\fR.

